03 Feb 2022
flag and switches
- identified by a hyphen and letter or word behind it
- flags and switches add functionality to  commands
ls -a
- this shows all hidden files in a directory
- -a is short for --all

--help can be used to find more information about a command
- to use "command_name" --help

man
- also known as the man pages
- using this man and the name of the command will bring up the manual page for that command.
- ex. man ls

